name: Inscription (free)
label: "By the Ocean"  He worked with hands both strong and true, Loved the ocean’s endless blue. Now he's gone, but still he stays, In every wave, in ocean's gaze. If you ever wish to speak to him, Put your feet in the ocean, feel the wind. He'll be there, where tides unfold, A quiet soul, both free and bold.
